Berlusconi Is ‘Innocent’ in Bribe Trial, Mills Tells Repubblica

-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 
2011-04-16T10:20:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/berlusconi-is-innocent-in-bribe-trial-mills-tells-repubblica.html
Italian Prime Minister  Silvio
Berlusconi  is “innocent” in a trial where he’s accused of
bribing U.K. lawyer David Mills to lie on his behalf under oath,
Mills told daily  la Repubblica .  “The only witness who can say that he’s guilty is me and I
say he’s innocent,” Mills said in the interview with the daily.
“I’m ready to answer questions in court if I’m called to
testify.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chiara Remondini in Milan at 
 cremondini@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
